=========================================================
How to use : from Yamagata-san's e-mail on Jul.27, 2013 (rev. 6369)


~yamagata/eb0

random_data_generator: 
Make data in a form of SendHeader+RawCopperHeader+RawCopperTrailer+SendTrailer and put to stdout
COPPER header is not made.

eb0: prototype of eb0. Read 1st word and take the value as the total length then send to downstream.


fetch_event: read data from stdin and check if data has SendHeader+RawCopperHeader+RawCopperTrailer+SendTrailer.
Read data is discarded.

Usage : 
Prepare 3 terminals.
1st: ./eb0 -n 2
2nd: nc -l 65000 | ./fetch_event
3rd: 
./random_event_generator -S 1280 -n 10000000 | nc 127.0.0.1 32000 &
./random_event_generator -S 6400 -n 10000000 | nc 127.0.0.1 32001 &
=========================================================
After changing a client-server role. Aug.16, 2013 (rev.6374)

Usage : 
Prepare 3 terminals.
1st: ./eb0 -n 2
2nd: nc 127.0.0.1 65000 | ./fetch_event
3rd: 
./random_event_generator -S 1280 -n 10000000 | nc -l 32000  &
./random_event_generator -S 6400 -n 10000000 | nc -l 32001 &


=========================================================
Connect basf2 program on COPPER
Usage : 
Prepare 4 terminals.
1st: ropc01% ./eb0 -n 1 -b
2nd: ropc01% ./RecvSendatROPC.sh
3rd: ropc01% nc 127.0.0.1 65000 > /dev/null

4th: cpr006% ./RecvSendCOPPER.sh


